	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001921_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'-->
<!--Hand 01 38 top left--><!--Hand 02 64757 top right--><!--Hand 03 D. Livingstone top center-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Cataracts</placeName><date when="1863-05-23">23<hi rend="sup">d</hi> May 1863</date></p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName><surname>Waller</surname></persName></p>
<lb/><p>Many thanks 
<lb/>for the kind invitation 
<lb/>to visit. I am not 
<lb/>insensible to the goodness 
<lb/>that prompted it, 
<lb/>but I am weak 
<lb/>&amp; disinclined to move 
<lb/>or speak. The <term type="ailment">diarrhoea</term>
<lb/>is ceasing and I 
<lb/>am afraid to risk 
<lb/>a relapse by sitting 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001921_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<lb/>in the canoe. I am 
<lb/>moreover recovering 
<lb/>as fast as may 
<lb/>be after losing so 
<lb/>much flesh.</p>
<lb/><p>The canoe came 
<lb/>yesterday afternoon 
<lb/>and I sent it 
<lb/>down again with 
<lb/>25 lbs of pork 
<lb/>&amp; 25 lbs of beef 
<lb/>and will be glad 
<lb/>of any<term type="insect"><unclear cert="medium" reason="hand">tsetse</unclear></term> meat 
<lb/>you can spare<supplied>.</supplied></p>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001921_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'-->
<lb/><p>It rained from 10 AM 
<lb/>yesterday right on 
<lb/>till dark and 
<lb/>threatens today as 
<lb/>if it had lost its 
<lb/>senses. If it was 
<lb/>as wet down at 
<lb/>the canoe I pity the 
<lb/><del type="strikethrough" cert="high">voagers</del> voyagers<supplied>.</supplied>
<lb/>If they meet 
<lb/>your <term type="note">mission</term>
<lb/>their coming 
<lb/>will be welcomed</p>
<lb/><p>Kindest salutations 
<lb/>to <persName>Proctor</persName> &amp; <unclear cert="high"><persName>Rowley </persName></unclear></p>
<lb/><p><persName>David <surname>Livingstone</surname></persName></p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001921_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
<lb/><p>Can you lend us a 
<lb/>rat trap? We have 
<lb/>3 kittens &amp; mean a 
<lb/>pair for you. 
<lb/>All our garden 
<lb/>seeds proved bad 
<lb/>save melons &amp; 
<lb/><choice><sic>cuccumbers</sic><corr>cucumbers</corr></choice> - which 
<lb/>are of a very 
<lb/>good kind<supplied>.</supplied></p>

	<pb n="0005" facs="liv_001921_0005"/><!--pb/@n='5'-->
<!-- hand 01 38 top left--><note type="editorial" anchored="true"><!-- hand 04-->notes in different hand</note>
<lb/><p><!-- different hand-->For <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">rs</hi></hi> G. <surname>Williams</surname></persName> with <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Horace 
<lb/><surname>Waller</surname></persName>'s kind regards.</p>
<lb/><p>Mem: This letter was written at 
<lb/><placeName><unclear cert="low" reason="copy">Ma Litti</unclear></placeName> at the foot of the Cataracts on 
<lb/>the <placeName><geogName type="river">Shir√©</geogName></placeName> river: the <persName>D<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi></persName> had been suffering 
<lb/>from a severe attack of <term type="ailment">Dysentery</term>
<lb/>just before. We were 12 miles below at 
<lb/><persName>Chibisa's</persName></p>
<lb/><p><persName>H W.</persName></p>
			
